From 6ccc915d9bfd0eea8496e05ba9a8c686c6c98246 Mon Sep 17 00:00:00 2001
From: Ganesh Kariganuru Mahabalesh <gkarigan@qti.qualcomm.com>
Date: Wed, 3 Sep 2025 14:14:19 -0700
Subject: [PATCH] QSDK:CP:wifi:ath12k:Fix incorrect monitor mode check in
 ath12k_vif_get_vp_num()

The function ath12k_vif_get_vp_num() checks ahvif->vdev_type to determine
if the interface is monitor type. However, this field is assigned later
in ath12k_mac_vdev_create(), causing the check to fail when
ath12k_vif_get_vp_num() is called earlier. This leads to call get_vp_num
op to get VP number for monitor interface from ath client.

Update the condition to check dev->ieee80211_ptr->iftype
against NL80211_IFTYPE_MONITOR, which is reliably set at the time
of the call.

Patch-dependency:
	0510-QSDK-DP-wifi-ath12k-Introduce-NSS-plugin-ops-for-Mod.patch

Fixes: I82f948368b6 (0510-QSDK-DP-wifi-ath12k-Introduce-NSS-plugin-ops-
for-Mod.patch)

Signed-off-by: Ganesh Kariganuru Mahabalesh <gkarigan@qti.qualcomm.com>
---
 drivers/net/wireless/ath/ath12k/ppe.c |    3 ++-
 1 file changed, 2 insertions(+), 1 deletion(-)

--- a/drivers/net/wireless/ath/ath12k/ppe.c
+++ b/drivers/net/wireless/ath/ath12k/ppe.c
@@ -1901,7 +1901,8 @@ int ath12k_vif_get_vp_num(struct ath12k_
 	int ppe_vp_num = ATH12K_INVALID_PPE_VP_NUM;
 	struct nss_plugins_ops *plugin_ops = ath12k_get_registered_nss_plugin_ops();
 
-	if (ahvif->vdev_type == WMI_VDEV_TYPE_MONITOR)
+	if (dev->ieee80211_ptr &&
+	    dev->ieee80211_ptr->iftype == NL80211_IFTYPE_MONITOR)
 		return 0;
 
 	if (!plugin_ops)
